content.problemStatement:
**Nested for loops** allow you to create **multi-level iterations** by placing one **for loop inside another**. This is particularly useful when working with **multi-dimensional data**, generating **patterns**, or performing **complex repetitive tasks** that require multiple levels of iteration.  

**Syntax:**  
```java
for (initialization1; condition1; update1) {  
    // Outer loop body

    for (initialization2; condition2; update2) {  
        // Inner loop body
    }
}
```
- **Outer loop** – Controls the number of main iterations.  
- **Inner loop** – Executes fully for each iteration of the outer loop.  

---

 **Example:**  
```java
class Seedit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Outer loop controls rows
        for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {  
            // Inner loop controls columns
            for (int j = 1; j <= 3; j++) {  
                System.out.print(j + " "); // Print column values
            }
            System.out.println(); // Move to the next line after printing a row
        }
    }
}
```

**Expected Output:**  
```default
1 2 3  
1 2 3  
1 2 3  
```

